===Etymology===
Halifax is believed to be a descendant of {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hāliġfeax|lit=holy hair}}. The town is said to have received the name from the fact that the hair of a murdered virgin was hung up on a tree in the neighborhood, which became a resort of pilgrims. Compare also {{l|en|Fairfax}}.

